<p>
<seg id=1> The international peace-keepers in Kosovo held out hope for a cease fire, though fighting between Serbian troops and the Albanian separatists has lasted several days. </seg>
<seg id=2> In Pristina on Monday a spokesman for the peace-keepers said that the present situation in the Yugoslavian province of Kosovo is peaceful. </seg>
<seg id=3> At least 12 people lost their lives in last week's fighting. </seg>
<seg id=4> The Polish Chairman of the European Security and Cooperation Council, Mr. Gelmerk, blamed both sides for causing the present outbreak of violence. </seg>
</p>
